  "title": "Inventory Management Executive | FMCG | 1 Year Contract",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client is a Government link company in the FMCG industry. Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a Inventory Management Executive to be part of their Warehouse team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the West.</strong></p><p>Duties of Inventory Management Executive:</p><ul><li><strong>Product & Stock Management</strong> – Verify product details, update system data, resolve discrepancies, and manage returns, exchanges, and disposals.</li><li><strong>Inventory & Transfers</strong> – Monitor RTV/RSTO activities, support replenishment, stock transfers, and DC relocations.</li><li><strong>Reporting & Data Maintenance</strong> – Maintain SKU info and provide regular reports on stock adjustments, damaged goods, and outstanding returns.</li><li><strong>Staff Administration & Development</strong> – Manage rosters, attendance, onboarding/resignation, welfare, and training programs.</li><li><strong>Safety & Security</strong> – Enforce workplace safety and security guidelines, conduct briefings, and support zero-accident initiatives.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Min 2 - 3 years of experience in inventory management from similar industry</li><li>Comfortable with 5 days rotating morning and afternoon shifts</li><li>Able to commit 1 year contract</li></ul><p><br />Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click <strong>APPLY NOW</strong> or email an updated copy of your resume / cv.</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</p><ul><li><strong>Email Address: jobs@recruitpedia.sg</strong></li><li>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</li><li>EA License No. 19C9682</li><li>EA Reg. No. R22108850 (Chan Mun Mun)</li></ul>",
